He's the military prosecutor who was in charge of

17
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:09,300
your parent's case twenty years ago. He played a part in covering up that trial.

18
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:14,400
Who said you could sit?

19
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:18,140
What's the matter with the ones who are subject to discipline?

20
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:22,970
I'll stand and receive it.

21
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:28,320
Let's first identify the persons subject to discipline. Name and rank?

22
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:31,180
4th Division Military Judicial Officer Captain Do Bae Man.

23
00:02:31,180 --> 00:02:34,510
4th Division Military Judicial Officer Captain Cha Wu In.

24
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:38,210
Captain Do Bae Man, Captain Cha Wu In.

25
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:43,440
We will start the disciplinary committee meeting on each charge against each of you.

26
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:45,290
Proceed.

27
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:52,010
You bastard. How far are you going to go?

28
00:02:52,010 --> 00:02:54,850
Do you think you can get away with this?

29
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:12,960
It's real.

30
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:16,040
It's a false leg.

31
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:24,580
You. You. Is this what you wanted to know?

32
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,360
It's General No Hwa Yeong.

33
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:12,360
Unity.

34
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:25,600
I'll ask the subject of discipline a question about the relevant facts of the incident.

35
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:29,150
Why did you break the prosthetic leg of Won Gi Chun, commander of the search squad?

36
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:32,210
In the process of investigating the shooting by Corporal Kim Han Yong,

37
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:35,520
a question arose concerning the search squad commander Won Gi Chun.

38
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,270
What was the question?

39
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:42,240
We determined that Commander Won Gi Chun had deceived the army and the nation.

40
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,920
Deceived?

41
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:47,860
Did you suspect the mine explosion in the DMZ was fabricated?

42
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:49,760
That is correct.

43
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,800
What is the basis?

44
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,870
The conclusion drawn from your statement is

45
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:58,200
that you broke his leg because the commander deceived everyone.

46
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:00,930
Well, did you even see a normal leg?

47
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:02,750
No.

48
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,200
No.

49
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,430
If that is so, were there any witnesses or informants?

50
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:10,870
No.

51
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:12,920
Are you kidding me now?

52
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:17,310
The entire country is outraged that military prosecutors insulted a national hero.

53
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:19,590
Without either evidence or a witness,

54
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:22,760
why on earth did you do something so ridiculous?

55
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,820
It's because I secured a video.

56
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,990
A video?

57
00:05:27,990 --> 00:05:32,380
It was a false report from an unknown source, Sir.

58
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:36,040
Did you prosecute a case based on false information?

59
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:40,190
Do you acknowledge your mistake?

60
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:46,640
I should have verified and confirmed the report.

61
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,100
It was my error.

62
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:52,890
I understood that Caption Cha Wu In performed all trial activities.

63
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:55,190
It was Captain Cha's first trial.

64
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:58,140
She was conducting the trial under my supervision.

65
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:05,040
I accept responsibility for everything in this incident as the senior prosecutor in the office.

66
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:12,120
What is your opinion as their immediate supervisor, General No Hwa Yeong?

67
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:16,100
On the basis of an unconfirmed report and without legal justification, two low-ranking military prosecutors

68
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:20,570
gave an indelible insult to a superior officer who had come to the courtroom as a victim.

69
00:06:20,570 --> 00:06:24,760
The only way to restore honor to Commander Won Gi Chun

70
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:30,170
is to punish Do Bae Man and Cha Wu In as a warning to others.

71
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:36,020
The disciplinary committee will vote on a decision after a ten minute recess.

72
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:48,140
Do you know what makes me maddest right now?

73
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:53,800
Is that that I was humiliated in court and will get punished?

74
00:06:56,980 --> 00:07:02,180
No. It's that I could not exercise my own judgment to stop you.

75
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:05,720
I think I'm going crazy because I am so pathetic.

76
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:09,300
I didn't consider that the video could be fake.

77
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,300
I am sorry.

78
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:17,840
The result of the committee's deliberation is that

79
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:20,160
we have determined that the abuse of authority

80
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:23,700
and violation of the duties to apply the laws and rules,

81
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:27,880
the duty of integrity and the duty to be dignified

82
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:31,370
by the subjects of discipline are grounds for discipline.

83
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:35,780
Accordingly, this disciplinary committee in compliance with Article 57 of the Military Personnel Act,

84
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:40,310
and the standards for disciplinary action under Article 2 of the Enforcement Rules of the Military Disciplinary Decree,

85
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:44,810
the subjects shall receive the following discipline.

86
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:47,180
Captain Do Bae Man, three months suspension,

87
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:49,670
Captain Cha Wu In, ten days confined to quarters.

88
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:51,470
That is all.

89
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:15,080
Three month's suspension, actually, is the longest suspension period.

90
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,800
Cha Wu In is also confined to the barracks.

91
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:21,640
She has to stay within the barracks until disciplinary action is completed.

92
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,790
She can't take a step beyond the guard post.

93
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:26,590
But if the order says don't leave the base,

94
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:30,770
does that mean she can't go to court? What do they want to do about investigations?

95
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:32,800
What do you mean what?

96
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,890
It means they need to stay off of cases.

97
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:38,970
Are you concerned about Cha Wu In now?

98
00:08:38,970 --> 00:08:42,150
She got a slap on the wrist thanks to Do Bae Man taking the fall.

99
00:08:42,150 --> 00:08:44,550
I'm sorry Chief.

100
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,700
But, speaking about that.

101
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:49,130
When Do Bae Man is suspended

102
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:52,090
and Cha Wu In is removed from her assignment,

103
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:56,200
who in our legal office is going take care of court issues?

104
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,410
- Who?
- Yes.

105
00:08:57,410 --> 00:08:59,220
What do you mean, who?

106
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:02,720
Me. I will take care of all of them.

107
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,320
Yes? Oh.

108
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:08,320
You Chief, are you saying you personally?

109
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:13,700
Sure. I will use this as an opportunity to take up the slack in the law office.

110
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:17,440
What are the cases that Cha Wu In was working on?

111
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,900
Kim Han Yong's shooting and No Tae Nam's desertion.

112
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:22,970
Both are on the same day.

113
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:24,130
That's good.

114
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:27,250
Put all the relevant material in my office.

115
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:30,350
Pardon? Yes!

116
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:34,960
I'm emphasizing once more,

117
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:39,910
in the future, even if there is one in our office, if you say the word "landmine" aloud,

118
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:44,150
I'll throw a harpoon at you!

119
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,380
A harpoon?

120
00:09:51,730 --> 00:09:53,590
I'm sick and tired of this.
(T/N: "Sick and tired" has same first syllable "ji" as "landmine.")

121
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:55,600
- Oh, "Ji"!
- That's not a joke!

122
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,790
Chief!

123
00:10:06,590 --> 00:10:10,880
It was strong evidence to break the story of the self-made hero.

124
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,730
His injury-free leg will do the job.

125
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:16,640
On the basis of an unconfirmed report and without legal justification two low-ranking military prosecutors

126
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:20,840
gave an indelible insult to a superior officer who had come to the courtroom as a victim.

127
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:24,530
I haven't slept a single day since you came to the law office.

128
00:10:24,530 --> 00:10:30,000
Stay out of all investigations until Prosecutor Do returns. Do you understand?

129
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,190
No. It's that I could not exercise my own judgment to stop you.

130
00:10:33,190 --> 00:10:38,760
I think I'm going crazy because I am so pathetic.

131
