137
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:11,600
The committee imposed a severe punishment on the military prosecutor who was the subject of the meeting.

138
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,980
Both the ruling and opposition parties are avidly trying to recruit

139
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:18,020
Lt. Colonel Won Gi Chun, Commander of the search squad who will be discharged shortly from the army,

140
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:23,610
as a candidate for the upcoming by-election by making a series of love calls to him.

141
00:11:23,610 --> 00:11:26,730
Not just within political circles, but everyone

142
00:11:26,730 --> 00:11:31,570
is watching to see where the hero Won Gi Chun will join hands.
[Attorney Yong Mun Gu]

143
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:44,040
I heard the news. Three months of suspension, right?

144
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:48,080
There's no way you came so late to have me cry on your shoulder. Why did you come?

145
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:51,100
If you were my subordinate, there would have been no disciplinary action

146
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,850
because I would have done it in advance.

147
00:11:54,850 --> 00:11:57,650
Are you here to tell me I should feel sorry for not working with you?

148
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:02,240
The Do Bae Man I know is not the sort of person

149
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:06,760
who would have broken Won Gi Chun's prosthetic leg without proof.

150
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,870
What is the reason?

151
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:12,160
You are very direct in your spying.

152
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:14,350
Did General No Hwa Yeong send you?

153
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:17,440
She hasn't said anything about it to me this time.

154
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:21,780
You're trying to get something out of me without any order from the general.

155
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:25,330
You're so twisted.

156
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:28,680
Anyway, I don't think you're in a good mood after the disciplinary action.

157
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:31,170
Although I feel sorry for you, thanks to the discipline,

158
00:12:31,170 --> 00:12:34,640
the desertion trial for No Tae Nam has been made easier.

159
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:38,880
Chief Seo Ju Hyeok is the prosecutor in place of Cha Wu In now.

160
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:43,270
Even if you were still in my employ, it could not have been a better situation than it is now.

161
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,880
It means you can never break a rock with an egg.

162
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:54,300
The more you think about it, the truer it is, right?

163
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,940
Military Prosecutor Do Bae Man

164
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:25,920
It hasn't been long since you canceled your discharge and returned. What's going on?

165
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:31,180
Why does our law office always get messed up? Why?

166
00:13:31,180 --> 00:13:35,690
While I'm away, take good care of the chief. Don't fight with each other.

167
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:38,350
Prosecutor Do Bae Man can't come into the base.

168
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:41,690
Prosecutor Cha Wu In can't leave the base.

169
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,470
I'm off.

170
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:58,730
This isn't some kind of star-crossed lovers' story.

171
00:13:58,730 --> 00:14:03,780
If someone were watching, they would think someone made a decision to separate the two. Seriously.

172
00:14:04,450 --> 00:14:07,840
We even gave Won Gi Chun the sympathy votes.

173
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:11,130
When he is discharged from the military, he will have an assemblyman's gold pin.

174
00:14:11,130 --> 00:14:16,410
And top of that, we can't even put an end to No Tae Nam with our own hands.

175
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,870
Why are you saying you are responsible for everything?

176
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:22,310
I made the mistake.

177
00:14:26,180 --> 00:14:27,980
I know that.

178
00:14:28,860 --> 00:14:31,960
This is what receiving discipline means.

179
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,290
It feels lousy.

180
00:14:37,090 --> 00:14:39,660
Why do I take all the responsibility for everything?

181
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:42,760
What would we do if both of us had our hands tied?

182
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:49,210
- Sorry?
- You in here and I outside will be doing something.

183
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:53,020
We failed but we didn't quit.

184
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:03,600
I won't give up the landmine case, either.

185
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:06,280
Besides, I made a promise to Pros Cha.

186
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,340
You said you would finish in ninety days, didn't you?

187
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:11,890
Right. I can't rest for ninety days.

188
00:15:11,890 --> 00:15:14,500
We need to wrap up the landmine case.

189
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:19,450
We both are excluded from our duties. I can't take any official action.

190
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:24,590
Things aren't always according to the book, both in investigations and in the world.

191
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:29,300
I am not someone who does as he is told. Don't you know me?

192
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,570
Call me.

193
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:49,420
I'm taking away the soldier and the prosecutor,

194
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:51,360
and moving as a civilian.

195
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:56,120
If you can't investigate officially, that means you can't stand out.

196
00:15:56,120 --> 00:16:02,250
Of course. I must look like a very decent civilian.

197
00:16:02,250 --> 00:16:04,680
That's why I came here first.

198
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:09,590
But, won't this fabric stand out too much, Mr. Prosecutor?

199
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:13,530
Clothes truly are wings.

200
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:17,670
No matter who sees me, I won't look like a military prosecutor. It's too perfect.

201
00:16:17,670 --> 00:16:20,230
You said it. Good job.

202
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:25,170
Let's return to the beginning and properly take Kim Han Yong's statement first.

203
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:29,390
After today's trial, I will send Kim Han Yong to you through Sang Gi.

204
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:37,840
Chief, it's time to go to court.

205
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:40,190
I washed and ironed it.

206
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:43,130
Chief, how many years has it taken for you to make a comeback?

207
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:45,340
Old soldiers never die.

208
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:48,150
They just disappear for a while and re-appear.

209
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:51,240
Old solider. Just hearing that warms my heart.

210
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:53,780
- May I try on?
- Yes.

211
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:55,970
Good.

212
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:58,040
All the time...

213
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:02,190
Starting now I will let you know some clues unofficially.

214
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:07,500
I'll get that and move from the outside. Okay?

215
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,640
Yes, General. We're leaving now.

216
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:14,960
I'll see you in court.

217
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,600
IM Defense Chairman Yong Mun Gu.

218
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:23,280
Get out of here immediately. I'm calling security.

219
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:26,550
Chairman No Tae Nam's stowaway funds.

220
00:17:27,830 --> 00:17:30,320
I personally processed them.

221
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:34,180
I have something to tell you. Please see me.

222
00:17:34,180 --> 00:17:36,250
Huh?

223
00:17:39,290 --> 00:17:43,520
- What the? Was I just ignored?
- You were.

224
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,260
Huh?

225
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:55,000
When you are a prosecutor or a lawyer,

226
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:58,390
you can only elegantly go up and down the courthouse stairs.

227
00:17:58,390 --> 00:18:01,370
However, you've become a big company owner now.

228
00:18:01,370 --> 00:18:04,800
Do you ever need to get your hands dirty?

229
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:09,520
Even if there is something hard to handle, and if I accept the work, it's going to be done smoothly.

230
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:14,990
Humble as I am, I only deal with the top 1%.

231
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:17,520
Did you help No Tae Nam stow away?

232
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:22,490
Well, besides helping him, I had a big fight with Doberman punk, too.

233
00:18:22,490 --> 00:18:25,450
Even Do Bae Man, we know each other.

234
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:28,490
The timing is good.

235
00:18:30,190 --> 00:18:32,980
I'll devote my heart and soul to you.

236
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:39,330
I'm make sure you don't even get a speck of dust on your hands.

237
00:18:53,990 --> 00:18:56,200
Starting now will we catch Do Bae Man?

238
00:18:56,200 --> 00:19:00,540
When I think about my reputation being ruined that day, I get angry and can't sleep.

239
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:05,540
The saying that there's nothing in the world that can't be thrown away is right.

240
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:06,980
What do you mean?

241
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:08,910
Thanks to shyster Do,

242
00:19:08,910 --> 00:19:13,310
we've joined CEO Yong Mun Gu's team now.

243
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:15,080
We finally made it to the big leagues!

244
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:16,960
Are we catching him or hot?

245
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:20,930
This stupid bastard, you don't understand anything.

