495
00:39:33,330 --> 00:39:34,610
I'm not joking around.

496
00:39:34,610 --> 00:39:36,740
Gosh, Aunt. Why are you doing this?

497
00:39:36,740 --> 00:39:39,400
Club Cartel. It was you, right?

498
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:44,320
I saw him from there. It's No Tae Nam's dog, right?

499
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:49,910
The rat that ran away after drinking with No Tae Nam. That was you, right Bae Man?

500
00:39:51,230 --> 00:39:52,830
Aunt.

501
00:39:53,990 --> 00:39:56,690
That's in the past now.

502
00:39:56,690 --> 00:39:58,510
The past?

503
00:40:03,590 --> 00:40:05,050
So it was you.

504
00:40:05,050 --> 00:40:07,760
About that...

505
00:40:08,520 --> 00:40:11,900
I was going to confess everything to you.

506
00:40:11,900 --> 00:40:14,950
I have something bigger to tell you before that.

507
00:40:14,950 --> 00:40:18,000
Something bigger? What is it?

508
00:40:19,770 --> 00:40:21,990
It's about Mom and Dad.

509
00:40:25,580 --> 00:40:28,960
- What?
- Where do I start.

510
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:31,890
Aunt. Listen carefully to me.

511
00:40:31,890 --> 00:40:35,780
Hey, get out. Get out now!

512
00:40:35,780 --> 00:40:38,010
You're going to use your parents as an excuse now?

513
00:40:38,010 --> 00:40:40,770
- That's not it. Just listen to me—
- Get out!

514
00:40:40,770 --> 00:40:43,720
- Go! I don't even want to look at you. Don't ever come here.
- You didn't even hear me out.

515
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:47,330
Take the dog too. Get out! Go!

516
00:40:47,330 --> 00:40:50,010
You don't have to shout. You're startling the dog.

517
00:40:50,010 --> 00:40:53,030
I said, get out! Go!

518
00:40:53,030 --> 00:40:55,580
I'm going. Gosh, you scared me.

519
00:40:55,580 --> 00:40:57,560
Let's go. Let's go.

520
00:40:57,560 --> 00:41:02,390
- Gosh, let's go. I'm going.
- Don't ever come again!

521
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:11,400
DMZ Landmine Explosion Case

522
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:15,040
It was written that Battalion Commander Won didn't save my brother.

523
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,840
But he shot him instead.

524
00:41:25,460 --> 00:41:30,540
Prosecutor Cha. I sent you the documents of the soldiers who went on the reconnaissance patrol.

525
00:41:34,710 --> 00:41:38,380
Officer Personnel Record

526
00:41:44,950 --> 00:41:46,440
Yes, Prosecutor Do?

527
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:50,310
CEO Kang is looking for the military doctor. We'll find a clue soon.

528
00:41:50,310 --> 00:41:54,340
I'm searching for potential suspects who could've sent the letter to Kim Han Yong.

529
00:41:56,170 --> 00:41:59,850
No Tae Nam's ruling is out.

530
00:41:59,850 --> 00:42:01,430
Kim Han Yong's too.

531
00:42:01,430 --> 00:42:02,840
I know.

532
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:07,900
No Tae Nam will get a slap on the wrist and start serving in the military.

533
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:10,950
Things don't always go to plan I guess.

534
00:42:10,950 --> 00:42:15,140
Wrong. Everything is going according to my plan.

535
00:42:15,140 --> 00:42:18,230
- What?
- Just wait and see.

536
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:25,140
I sent his worst nightmare to his side, so he can enjoy his military life.

537
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:34,740
I'm Sergeant Ahn Su Ho. You're the famous No Tae Nam, right?

538
00:42:36,570 --> 00:42:39,580
Gosh, we went to the same military prison and now the same base.

539
00:42:39,580 --> 00:42:43,300
I guess it's fate. I hope we get along.

540
00:42:46,620 --> 00:42:49,380
Seems like you're not hoping for the same?

541
00:42:49,380 --> 00:42:55,320
From now on, you'll have to serve more diligently than anyone else.

542
00:42:55,320 --> 00:42:58,990
This is the last chance I'll be giving you.

543
00:43:00,310 --> 00:43:03,260
I hope we get along.

544
00:43:03,260 --> 00:43:04,820
Sergeant Ahn Su Ho.

545
00:43:04,820 --> 00:43:09,310
All right, Tae Nam. You can be comfortable around me.

546
00:43:44,090 --> 00:43:47,920
Barracks 1

547
00:43:50,570 --> 00:43:54,780
All right, the platoon members will be back once they're done with their duties. Wait for them.

548
00:43:54,780 --> 00:43:57,180
Yes, I understand.

549
00:43:57,850 --> 00:44:00,970
Hey, don't you answer me?

550
00:44:00,970 --> 00:44:03,960
You clueless newbie.

551
00:44:03,960 --> 00:44:05,450
I get it.

552
00:44:05,450 --> 00:44:07,440
Get it right.

553
00:44:20,180 --> 00:44:22,330
Is this base at the frontline?

554
00:44:22,330 --> 00:44:27,220
The exact name is GOP (Troops beyond the barbed wire fence). It's a platoon that protects the border 24-7.

555
00:44:27,220 --> 00:44:29,180
It's different from regular troops.

556
00:44:29,180 --> 00:44:32,980
- How is it different?
- There's no PX beyond the FEBA base.

557
00:44:32,980 --> 00:44:35,880
There's no leaving or sleeping outside of the base either.

558
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:38,170
So what does this place have?

559
00:44:38,170 --> 00:44:41,230
Real bullets and grenades.

560
00:44:41,230 --> 00:44:43,310
G-Grenades?

561
00:44:43,310 --> 00:44:46,710
What? Are you scared?

562
00:44:49,920 --> 00:44:52,190
You'd better lay low here.

563
00:44:52,190 --> 00:44:58,210
They live amongst grenades here. If there's conflict, they'll blow the grenade right away.

564
00:45:01,380 --> 00:45:06,480
But what got you into military prison, Sergeant Ahn?

565
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:08,000
Me?

566
00:45:11,550 --> 00:45:13,400
Are you curious?

567
00:45:16,820 --> 00:45:19,290
I'll tell you little by little.

568
00:45:22,460 --> 00:45:25,190
Hey, new ones, new ones!

569
00:45:25,190 --> 00:45:26,620
Wow, is he a celebrity?

570
00:45:26,620 --> 00:45:28,620
- Look at his face.
- What's with the stare?

571
00:45:28,620 --> 00:45:32,360
- It's like you want to fight us.
- Are you No Tae Nam?

572
00:45:36,790 --> 00:45:39,100
Wow, I won!

573
00:45:42,030 --> 00:45:45,840
Man, you must've done all sorts of things to pay money to gamble.

574
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:49,600
For example, something like switching the CT scan pictures.

575
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,540
Shit.

576
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:54,540
Shyster Do.

577
00:45:55,900 --> 00:46:00,230
You must be short on money since receiving punishment, seeing how you're here to rip him off.

578
00:46:00,230 --> 00:46:02,770
What? Why are you doing it to me?

579
00:46:02,770 --> 00:46:05,740
- Are you all in the same gang?
- No.

580
00:46:06,390 --> 00:46:08,860
Why are you interested in him?

581
00:46:08,860 --> 00:46:13,190
There's an old saying about one's lack of knowledge. You probably wouldn't know.

582
00:46:13,190 --> 00:46:18,170
You mean the saying, "How can a summer bug know the winter?"

583
00:46:18,170 --> 00:46:21,590
Wow, our Doberman is so smart.

584
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:26,460
You've received an order from someone else to bring him in.

585
00:46:26,460 --> 00:46:31,610
So it means, you're a thoughtless bug who just does as you're told to do.

586
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:35,150
- Bug?
- Yes.

587
00:46:37,900 --> 00:46:42,830
Hey, Do Bae Man. You don't know my life.

588
00:46:42,830 --> 00:46:46,650
Meaning I live according to my own thoughts too!

589
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:47,500
Come with me.

590
00:46:47,700 --> 00:46:49,500
Take him out!

591
00:46:59,420 --> 00:47:01,240
Comrade Do.

592
00:47:03,050 --> 00:47:07,260
I'll finally get my revenge for the last time.

593
00:47:10,970 --> 00:47:13,480
I'm sick of this. So sick of it.

594
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:16,690
That damn bastard.

595
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:32,030
He's cute now that I've seen him again.

596
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:38,620
Excuse me. Was it this guy who was looking for Military Doctor Cho?

597
00:47:38,620 --> 00:47:42,460
Oh, gosh. You're the guy who came last time. Are you okay?

598
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:45,250
- Is it this person, right?
- No.

599
00:47:45,250 --> 00:47:47,530
- You need to treat it right now.
- No, no!!

600
00:47:47,530 --> 00:47:49,990
Are you sure you're not mistaken? It must've been him.

601
00:47:49,990 --> 00:47:52,370
How can I confuse that man with this gangster.

602
00:47:52,370 --> 00:47:55,970
That person was a total gentleman.

603
00:47:55,970 --> 00:47:57,660
Perhaps,

604
00:47:58,720 --> 00:48:00,890
is this person?

605
00:48:00,890 --> 00:48:04,130
Right. Yes, he is.

606
00:48:04,130 --> 00:48:06,890
- You're sure, right?
- Of course.

607
00:48:06,890 --> 00:48:09,450
I get it. Thank you.

608
00:48:13,190 --> 00:48:15,680
Military Doctor Cho is in Yong Mun Gu's hands?

609
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:18,260
- Then is No Hwa Yeong—
- No.

610
00:48:18,260 --> 00:48:21,520
He didn't know about Won Gi Chun's incident at all.

611
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:24,550
The Do Bae Man I know is not the sort of person

612
00:48:24,550 --> 00:48:30,070
who would have broken Won Gi Chun's prosthetic leg without proof. What is the reason?

613
00:48:30,070 --> 00:48:34,730
If No Hwa Yeong ordered him to do it, he wouldn't run around personally like me.

614
00:48:34,730 --> 00:48:38,470
So Yong Mun Gu is acting without orders from No Hwa Yeong?

615
00:48:38,470 --> 00:48:43,620
Like us, Yong Mu Gu is curious about the landmine incident.

616
00:48:43,620 --> 00:48:47,420
Anyway, it's a problem that we can't use the military doctor to our advantage now.

617
00:48:47,420 --> 00:48:49,760
I'll give you an even better advantage.

618
00:48:49,760 --> 00:48:52,360
Did you find the suspect who sent him the letter?

619
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:54,600
I'll give you the address.

620
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:56,390
Yes.

621
00:49:02,230 --> 00:49:04,010
Yes, ma'am.

622
00:49:28,250 --> 00:49:31,670
I've already warmed him up for you.

623
00:49:31,670 --> 00:49:34,270
He'll spill whatever you ask him.

624
00:49:34,270 --> 00:49:36,490
Not bad.

625
00:49:36,490 --> 00:49:39,630
From now on, you'll follow me like a shadow.

626
00:49:39,630 --> 00:49:41,960
Like someone who's there but undetectable.

627
00:49:41,960 --> 00:49:45,900
Undetectable? I like that.

628
00:49:45,900 --> 00:49:50,340
It sounds like you'll take care of everything, sir.

629
00:49:52,850 --> 00:49:58,770
You must've hid the company commander's CT scan because there was information that had to be hidden.

630
00:49:58,770 --> 00:50:03,310
It was because his brain had a bullet inside, not shrapnel.

631
00:50:03,310 --> 00:50:06,790
Yes, that's right.

632
00:50:06,790 --> 00:50:09,520
Did Won Gi Chun order you to do it?

633
00:50:09,520 --> 00:50:12,330
Yes, yes.

634
00:50:12,330 --> 00:50:14,370
It wasn't ordered by someone higher up?

635
00:50:14,370 --> 00:50:18,330
No, sir. I received the order from the battalion commander.

636
00:50:18,330 --> 00:50:20,900
You sure? That there's no one else besides Won Gi Chun?

637
00:50:20,900 --> 00:50:22,640
Yes.

638
00:50:25,070 --> 00:50:29,670
Then let's get to the main point now.

639
00:50:29,670 --> 00:50:33,760
- Pardon?
- Tell me about Won Gi Chun's leg.

640
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:44,630
Okay.

641
00:50:52,340 --> 00:50:56,980
Today's Midnight Snack

642
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:01,870
It's cold.

643
00:51:03,890 --> 00:51:06,150
I am hungry.

644
00:51:07,560 --> 00:51:10,730
You're Sergeant Gu Yeong Seok from 4th Division, right?

645
00:51:10,730 --> 00:51:14,310
Man, it's cold. Did you receive a lot of orders today?

646
00:51:14,310 --> 00:51:19,180
- What's your deal?
- You're the one who left the letter at the company commander's hospital room, right?

647
00:51:21,050 --> 00:51:24,410
- Who are you really?
- Me?

648
00:51:25,940 --> 00:51:29,410
I'm the military prosecutor who was in charge of Kim Han Yong's case.

649
00:51:29,410 --> 00:51:32,240
Answer the question.

650
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:36,140
- No.
- Did you say no?

651
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:41,710
If it really wasen't you, wouldn't you ask what letter I'm talking about?

652
00:51:41,710 --> 00:51:45,650
So this means you know what letter I'm talking about.

653
00:51:45,650 --> 00:51:48,850
Don't go there. It's none of my business.

654
00:51:48,850 --> 00:51:53,020
The day you left the letter happened to be the day you were discharged.

655
00:51:53,020 --> 00:51:56,230
Gosh, what a coincidence, right?

656
00:51:56,230 --> 00:51:58,350
Even the handwriting matches yours.

657
00:51:59,600 --> 00:52:03,340
Why then? You weren't confident enough to do it in uniform?

658
00:52:03,340 --> 00:52:09,010
Or did you want to rid of your petty guilt?

659
00:52:09,010 --> 00:52:13,250
So? Did it rid of your guilt?

660
00:52:13,250 --> 00:52:16,420
Shut your mouth! I was already discharged!

661
00:52:16,420 --> 00:52:19,500
You. You have no right to do this to me.

662
00:52:19,500 --> 00:52:23,210
I'm never going to get tied in with the damn military ever again.

663
00:52:23,210 --> 00:52:26,820
The letter you wrote became a trigger to Kim Han Yong.

664
00:52:29,900 --> 00:52:34,130
He read that letter and shot Won Gi Chun.

665
00:52:34,130 --> 00:52:36,840
He received a five-year sentence for that.

666
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:40,210
- Five years, you said?
- You shouldn't have left the letter behind.

667
00:52:40,210 --> 00:52:43,830
How do you plan to rid of your guilt regarding Kim Han Yong now?

668
00:52:44,790 --> 00:52:47,650
You said it's been decided. Isn't it all over now?

669
00:52:47,650 --> 00:52:49,320
No.

670
00:52:51,730 --> 00:52:56,450
I'm going to start again. I heard you relied on the company commander the most.

671
00:52:56,450 --> 00:53:01,020
Even if the military sucks, you can't let it slide just like that, right?

672
00:53:04,700 --> 00:53:07,920
You're the only hope that the company commander has.

673
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:10,460
Please tell me the truth.

674
00:53:15,210 --> 00:53:20,480
It was extremely foggy that day, so it was difficult to secure clear vision.

675
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:22,850
Halt. Five minute rest.

676
00:53:22,850 --> 00:53:23,850
Five minute rest.

677
00:53:23,850 --> 00:53:25,650
- Five minute rest.
- Five minute rest.

678
00:53:25,650 --> 00:53:33,800
During the reconnaissance, Battalion Commander Won went to relieve himself.

679
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:36,790
Then a water elk appeared.

680
00:53:39,690 --> 00:53:42,300
Isn't that a water elk?

681
00:53:42,300 --> 00:53:44,690
- It looks like one.
- What?

682
00:53:46,150 --> 00:53:48,180
Isn't it heading towards the battalion commander?

683
00:53:48,180 --> 00:53:49,630
Yes, I think you're right.

684
00:53:49,630 --> 00:53:54,320
That's a mine field. If the water elk steps on a mine, it'll be bad.

685
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:56,690
Hey. You boys wait over here.

686
00:53:56,690 --> 00:54:00,430
- Stay on your toes.
- Yes, sir.

687
00:54:01,240 --> 00:54:04,200
I'll go together with you, Company Commander.

688
00:54:06,110 --> 00:54:07,980
Stay here.

689
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:21,490
Who is it?

690
00:54:22,380 --> 00:54:24,350
Company Commander?

691
00:54:32,870 --> 00:54:34,850
I said, who are you!

692
00:54:34,850 --> 00:54:36,770
I'm going to shoot if you don't give me your name and rank.

693
00:54:36,770 --> 00:54:38,570
You hear me?

694
00:54:52,190 --> 00:54:56,080
- Battalion Commander!
- I said, I'll shoot!

695
00:55:22,710 --> 00:55:24,510
Company Commander?

696
00:55:24,510 --> 00:55:26,440
Company Commander!

697
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:43,410
If the case really gets re-investigated,

698
00:55:43,410 --> 00:55:47,880
I'll testify to everything in trial.

699
00:55:50,620 --> 00:55:52,840
I'll see you in court.

700
00:55:54,510 --> 00:55:57,700
If Sergeant Gu's testimony is true,

701
00:55:57,700 --> 00:56:01,790
Won Gi Chun shot the company commander accidentally.

702
00:56:01,790 --> 00:56:04,410
Then he transformed himself into the Landmine Hero to cover that incident up.

703
00:56:04,410 --> 00:56:07,260
Division Commander No Hwa Yeong was involved?

704
00:56:07,260 --> 00:56:11,670
They could've just punished Won Gi Chun alone. Why did they go through all that trouble?

705
00:56:11,670 --> 00:56:16,780
If a shooting accident happens in the DMZ, it won't stop at just Won Gi Chun.

706
00:56:16,780 --> 00:56:21,360
It happened right after she was inaugurated as division commander, which she had dreamed of for so long.

707
00:56:21,360 --> 00:56:23,840
Then No Tae Nam's deserting case happened soon after.

708
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:28,600
So she manipulated the incident and turned Won Gi Chun into the Landmine Hero.

709
00:56:29,260 --> 00:56:32,850
Hold on. Then what about this issue?

710
00:56:39,850 --> 00:56:43,110
I ran it through a program, but found no traces of modifications or that it's fake.

711
00:56:43,110 --> 00:56:45,440
You'll get the same results even if the NFS checks it.

712
00:56:45,440 --> 00:56:51,840
Sergeant Gu's testimony too. He said Won Ki Chun didn't hurt his leg that day.

713
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:53,890
Then why did his leg disappear?

714
00:56:53,890 --> 00:56:59,800
I think he cut off his leg before the trial.

715
00:57:00,780 --> 00:57:03,020
There's no other explanation besides that.

716
00:57:03,020 --> 00:57:04,670
What?

717
00:57:04,670 --> 00:57:07,250
He c-cut off his leg?

718
00:57:07,250 --> 00:57:15,190
We might be dealing with a monster that's much more terrifying than we had imagined.

719
00:57:42,970 --> 00:57:46,090
Chairman No has been assigned to his base safely.

720
00:57:46,090 --> 00:57:49,990
You have to always be on alert for both Tae Nam and IM Defense.

721
00:57:49,990 --> 00:57:55,370
Your job is to prevent accidents from happening.

722
00:58:00,490 --> 00:58:05,810
I found something out about Lieutenant Colonel Won's mine case.

723
00:58:05,810 --> 00:58:11,560
I'm sure I made it clear to keep your nose out of my division and soldiers.

724
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:14,740
Did it not sound like a warning to you?

725
00:58:14,740 --> 00:58:19,360
I did it to prevent an accident, just like you told me to.

726
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:24,110
As the CEO of IM Defense and your lawyer.

727
00:58:26,570 --> 00:58:30,440
All right. What did you find out?

728
00:58:32,500 --> 00:58:38,880
The real main character of the Landmine Hero's story was you, but not Won Gi Chun.

729
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:42,170
An accidental shooting happened in a mine field.

730
00:58:42,170 --> 00:58:46,510
If the world found out,

731
00:58:46,510 --> 00:58:50,630
you would've experienced the humiliation of stepping down from your position as soon as you got it.

732
00:58:50,630 --> 00:58:53,430
On top of that, Chairman No's trial happened.

733
00:58:53,430 --> 00:58:57,370
Which is why I made Won Gi Chun a hero?

734
00:58:58,760 --> 00:59:00,900
You've got a good imagination Lawyer Yong.

735
00:59:00,900 --> 00:59:04,610
I'm already certain of those facts.

736
00:59:05,740 --> 00:59:09,990
I'm actually extremely curious about something else.

737
00:59:09,990 --> 00:59:12,610
Won Gi Chun's leg.

738
00:59:28,060 --> 00:59:31,780
Save me, Division Commander. I'll do as you order.

739
00:59:31,780 --> 00:59:35,510
I'll do anything. Whatever it is, I'll do it.

740
00:59:35,510 --> 00:59:40,410
That's right. You have to do everything.

741
00:59:41,270 --> 00:59:43,420
